  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The CORDA dataset, hosted on Zenodo and authored by a collaborative team from leading cardiology institutions, has garnered attention with 762 views and 351 downloads, indicating its utility and interest within the research community.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The CORDA Dataset (2023) represents a significant resource within cardiovascular research, originating from a collaboration of esteemed institutions such as the Centro Cardiologico Monzino and the Ospedale di Parma. This dataset is publicly accessible via Zenodo, demonstrating a commitment to open data practices. With 762 views and 351 downloads, it exhibits a promising degree of interest and engagement from the research community, reflecting its potential as a valuable asset for further studies.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Although there are no citations or online mentions on platforms such as Reddit or Wikipedia, the dataset's engagement metrics indicate that it is being utilized in research contexts. The record of 351 downloads signifies a level of active community reuse, which highlights its technical value and accessibility. This foundational output provides researchers with key insights that could foster advancements in cardiovascular health.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Another salient aspect is the collaborative effort among notable institutions, which enhances the credibility and reach of the dataset. The involvement of multiple reputable hospitals ensures a diverse level of expertise and data integrity that can benefit ongoing research initiatives. As the dataset has demonstrated proven downstream reuse, it is contributing to subsequent studies, thereby amplifying its impact and relevance in the scientific community.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">In summary, the CORDA dataset exemplifies a significant stride in open scientific practice, with concrete evidence of engagement through active downloads. While it currently lacks citations or mentions in social discourse, the solid interest reflected in its access metrics underscores its potential role in advancing understanding in the field of cardiology.</p>",
